      "score": 98,
      "comments": 17,
      "author": "stapelberg",
      "published": "2026-05-24T14:38:34Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Rewriting rsync in Go mitigates class-wide memory corruption bugs like buffer overflows inherent in legacy C implementations.",
        "Go's strict path cleaning libraries natively prevent directory traversal exploits, a frequent security flaw in traditional rsync clients.",
        "A minimal feature set reduces the attack surface by avoiding complex, legacy protocol features prone to parser vulnerabilities."
      ]
